<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-23T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4701: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-23T13:00:00-04:00">July 23, 1931—1
                                    p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>234. For Secretary Stimson.</p>
                            <p>“I wish to convey to you my sincere congratulations. My appreciation
                                is the deeper from knowing the complexity of the difficulties which
                                confronted you over the past 10 days and the able manner they have
                                been surmounted. I hope you may now secure a real rest. Herbert
                                Hoover”.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castile</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>